    "α = -3.5, as found in Abbott et al. (2023c).",
    "This definition of local Universe is purely arbitrary and chosen for visualisation purposes.",
    "The non-parametric reconstruction is consistent with the power-law distribution in the 10 ∼ 40 M region, up to redshift z ∼ 0.13, with cutoffs at both ends of the mass spectrum.",
    "At larger redshift, the distribution starts to deviate from the simple power-law behaviour, transitioning towards the ∼35 M Gaussian-like feature.",
    "Given this qualitative agreement between our reconstruction and the power-law reported by Abbott et al. (2023c), we suggest that the PowerLaw+Peak model is actually driven by the local merger rate density, with a contribution to the Gaussian peak from the BHs further away in look-back time."
